some time design pattern get miss used,
every pattern has a context, a specific problem to solve!
if you just blindly apply these pattern you just increase complexity
without any improvement!
we called it "Design Smell" in Application.(Application with overly complicated design)
Just understand problem, and understand design pattern how solve it!


Example
we have a stopwatch class (has a button to strat/stop):
public void click(){
    if (isRunning){
        isRunning = false;
        System.out.println("Stopped");
    } else{
        isRunning = true;
        System.out.println("Running");
    }
}



we may think, the click method is behaving differently
"depending on the state of the stopwatch"
so that is the case for State Pattern
(see abuse package!)

Note: our if/els statement on stopwatch class
      was so simple. if we have a few decision making branches in a method
      we don't need Sate pattern!
      (and we know stopwatch is not going t have new state in future!
       click method just for stop and run the watch
       we will not have extension)